    {
      "type": "header",
      "level": 1,
      "text": "Antimicrobial Stewardship"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Uncomplicated adenitis in children usually resolves without treatment, although one study showed faster resolution with azithromycin (Ped Infect Dis J 1998; 17:447). Joint decision making about benefits and downsides of treatment is reasonable."
    },
    {
      "type": "header",
      "level": 1,
      "text": "Comments"
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "items": [
        "Jarisch-Herxheimer reactions have occurred after the first few doses of antibiotic.",
        "Remember to check for drug-drug interactions in patients given Rifampin.",
        "Review: Pediatr Infect Dis J 2021,40:S11."
      ]
    }
